HEADWORD: Mentha
<hw>Men"tha</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Mint</er> the plant.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A widely
distributed genus of fragrant herbs, including the peppermint,
spearmint, etc. The plants have small flowers, usually arranged in dense
axillary clusters.</def>⟦br⟧
